cs.RO, cs.ME, cs.SY, cs.ROB, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper discusses the workspace analysis of two parallel mechanisms designed for machining applications. This falls under the domain of robotics and hence, cs.RO is the most likely sub-category. 
2. cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering): The paper deals with the design and analysis of mechanical systems, specifically parallel mechanisms. Hence, cs.ME is also a likely sub-category. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the kinetostatic performances of the parallel mechanisms, which involves control and system analysis. Hence, cs.SY is also a possible sub-category. 
4. cs.ROB (Robotics and Automation): The paper deals with the design and analysis of robotic systems, specifically parallel mechanisms. Hence, cs.ROB is also a possible sub-category. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses interval analysis based methods to compute the dextrous workspace and the largest cube enclosed in this workspace. This involves computational methods and hence, cs.CE is a possible sub-category.
